episodes.summary: Comptroller Gilbert Gottfried warms up Harmontown's biggest crowd yet at New York City's 92y!

episodes.title: 120 - LIVE in Toronto feat. Bobcat Goldthwait!
episodes.summary: Harmontown visits Toronto for a massive show with comptroller Bobcat Goldthwait! Later, our friend Jane comes on stage to talk transgenderism.

episodes.title: 119 - LIVE at the Vista with bonus Q&A
episodes.summary: In conjunction with Cinefamily and Starburns Industries, enjoy Harmontown, LIVE from the Vista theater with a special Q&A for the HARMONTOWN movie, now at harmontown.com!

episodes.title: 118 - LIVE from Seattle 2014 feat. Dino Stamatopoulos!
episodes.summary: Harmontown kicks of its run of movie screenings followed by a live podcast in Seattle to a powerful crowd of Harmenians and is post lifted to new heights and derailed from its first guest comptrolling appearance from Dino Stamatopoulos!

episodes.title: 117 - Debbie Request Permission To Do Dallas
episodes.summary: Harmontown tests its live streaming capabilities, Alex Rubens comptrolls and instead of D&D the group goes on a sci-fi side quest.

episodes.title: 116 - LIVE From The XOXO Festival 2014 in Portland
episodes.summary: Technology! Industry! Vodka! Harmontown live in Portland from the XOXO Festival with Spencer as your humble comptroller!

episodes.title: 115 - Oh, the Blimpery!
episodes.summary: Dolphins are bad, Jews are great as learn with comptroller, Rick & Morty writer Ryan Ridley! Then for the first time we welcome our hilarious friend Dave Horwitz to the stage who you all now can begin to fall for. In D&D, its really funny.

episodes.title: 114 - Slick Rick & The Batman
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon pays an Australian in the audience 100 bucks to serve them cups of ice. We get to the bottom of Schrabbing with Internet Trolling Sensation Rob Schrab and later, Rob provides all sound effects for D&D.

episodes.title: 113 - FlagCop
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon is possibly a bit jealous of Spencer and Real Abed's budding friendship, and later we welcome Demorge Brown to the mix which spawns a TV pilot pitch, "FlagCop".

episodes.title: 112 - Popeye Is Our Lord And Savior
episodes.summary: Harmontown is not ready to say goodbye to our friend Robin WIlliams; Jeff & Dan write a new song, an Emmy award winning special effects editor makes their way to the stage, Ferguson and the current paramilitary police state are discussed at length. You ready? Lets do this.

episodes.title: 111 - Fluid Levitation
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon, Jeff Davis, Erin McGathy and Spencer Crittenden discover a Belgian fan in the audience, but when a Londoner from the crowd

episodes.title: 110 - Dana Carvey Has Never Done Anything Wrong (feat. Tenacious D)
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon welcomes Dana Carvey to Harmontown who for some reason apologizes for Wayne's World two and out of nowhere, Tenacious D of www.festivalsupreme.com appear out of thin air! In D&D, someone dies.

episodes.title: 109 - Jaime Lannister's Hand
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon discusses ComicCon, we enter the Animal Corner, finds out Rogaine will kill your cat and Kumail returns just in time for a rousing round of D&D.

episodes.title: 108 - I Make A 5 Stars
episodes.summary: Mayor Dan Harmon and Comptroller Duncan Trussell makes another sold out show at Nerdmelt Theater one for the ages!

episodes.title: 107 - Clever Girl
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon perfects the apology, Erin McGathy runs an epic Game Corner and in D&D the gang encounter a black dragon.

episodes.title: 106 - Pakisnap!
episodes.summary: Dan Harmon, Jeff Davis, Greg Proops, Kumail Nanjiani, Erin McGathy and Spencer Crittenden perform for another sold out HARMONTOWN and FINALLY, necrophillia is discussed at great length.

episodes.title: 105 - Game Recognize Game
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon enters couples therapy and makes an emotional bid. Kumail Nanjiani is back and doesn't understand why Jeff talks to strangers. Doctors are too prostate happy and a Brazilian fan from Rio defends them. Just a great episode from top to bottom, enjoy.

episodes.title: 104 - Death To Superman
episodes.summary: Its just Mayor Harmon, Jeff and Spencer and Dan catches you up in World Cup corner and later, Dan improvises his own Superman movie. In D&D, the gang becomes a literal gang and finally loots.

episodes.title: 103 - Tony Shalhoub Award
episodes.summary: Happy Birthday to all the Fathers out there, Kumail is comptrolling, Erin runs her best game yet and D&D is sizzling. Come get your Harmontown!

episodes.title: 102 - Sleepy Canyoneer
episodes.summary: Tony Danza can read Dan's tweets; everyone shares crying stories and there is a sleepy canyoneer in the crowd.

episodes.title: 101 - Paloma
episodes.summary: A hungover stroll through such topics as bumper stickers, misogyny, Wolfenstein and how horrifying that game must be for Germans. Kumail Nanjiani's back and we welcome DeMorge Brown to the stage!

episodes.title: 100 - Boner-Hurt Kansas
episodes.summary: It is the Centepisodial Spectacular of Harmontown! Adam Goldberg runs a quiz against a super fan and your Mayor to see who knows more about Harmontown.

episodes.title: 99 - Live From Bridgetown 2014!
episodes.summary: Live from The Bridgetown Festival in Portland, Oregon; Harmontown is now in session!

episodes.title: 98 - HARMONOLOGY
episodes.summary: Hot off the Renaissance Faire, the whole gang is back from hiatus... and very drunk. Kumail Nanjiani and Matt Gourley join the stage while Mayor Harmon proposes a new religion.

episodes.title: 97 - Long Brown Blood
episodes.summary: Preparing for its first month hiatus, Harmontown goes for a big blow out that tackles the usual; racism, censorship, health, mortality etc. Spencer returns for D&D to promote Friendship & Cigarettes.

episodes.title: 96 - SWAN OF DURG-A-DURG
episodes.summary: Following the 826LA charity event, Mayor Harmon is met by an agent of compromise when a psychologist takes the stage. Later, Erin McGathy attempts her first Dungeon Mastering in D&D!

episodes.title: 95 - Bill Martigans
episodes.summary: The Harmontown dream team; Dan Harmon, Jeff Bryan Davis, Erin McGathy, Mitch Hurwitz and Kumail Nanjiani recap SXSW; Fred Phelps death bed and later, Spencer returns for a roaring session of D&D!

episodes.title: 94 - Live From SXSW '14 + Movie Q&A
episodes.summary: From Austin, TX, Harmontown is live from the Liberty Tavern and SXSW. Bonus audio from the Q & A following the premiere of the "Harmontown" documentary.

episodes.title: 93 - McConaissance
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon tearfully reflects on the passing of Harold Ramis and while the Academy Awards ceremony takes place mere blocks away, Harmontown hosts its own Oscars special.

episodes.title: 92 - It's Not Personal, It's Business
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon becomes label mates with Ice-T, which spurs Comptroller Jeff Davis into having  Dan rattle off all his impressions. Mitch Hurwitz joins the group and when Spencer is out for the week, an abstract game of D&D ensues.

episodes.title: 91 - Net Neutrality/Butt Fun
episodes.summary: Net Neutrality activist Eddie Geller shines a light onto how our rights online are on their way out. This, naturally, agitates Mayor Harmon's disenchantment with bureaucracy and capitalism. Meanwhile, Comptroller Jeff Davis and Kumail Nanjiani attempt to come up with something better to call it than "net neutrality."

episodes.title: 90 -  CyberChrist and Stubnortz
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon has some qualms with Uber, we check in with Adam Goldberg and SuperEgo's Matt Gourley settles a dispute during D&D.

episodes.title: 89 - Live At Cobb's in San Francisco with Joel Hodgson
episodes.summary: Harmontown does the 13th annual San Francisco Sketchfest, gets a drop in from Mystery Science Theater 3000's Joel Hodgson and later on, the show goes straight Maury Povich.

episodes.title: 88 - My Whole Life Is A Smile
episodes.summary: Harmontown commemorates Phillip Seymour Hoffman, discusses happiness, takes a Sports Corner break and in Pathfinder, Laan-Ev introduces the gang to his friends.

episodes.title: 87 - Kiss Doesn't Get The Joke
episodes.summary: Guest Comptroller Mitch Hurwitz does his best to help Mayor Harmon and Kumail Nanjiani ridicule Rob Schrab as he tries to celebrate 20 years of his comic book SCUD: The Disposable Assassin. In D&D, Sharpie and Laan-ev go to blows.

episodes.title: 86 - Constitutional Belieber
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon is joined by Alie & Georgia of the Slumber Party podcast to defend the constitutional rights of Justin Bieber. In D&D, Sharpie doesn't like Lineve's tone.

episodes.title: 85 - Gender Neutrality
episodes.summary: A mysterious package sparks a conversation about gender roles in our society; and upon colonizing the moon, is it even possible to raise children gender neutral? Later, Jeff shares kind of a f****d up story.

episodes.title: 84 - Low Jack For Your Back Pack, Crackerjack!
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon and his Comptroller Jeff Davis return from Scotland where Dan proposed to Erin McGathy. Then, uhh, Mitch Hurwitz, Harris Wittels, Kumail Nanjiani and Steve Agee join the stage... stop reading and get in here!

episodes.title: 83 - DICKS AND BALLS AND BEER
episodes.summary: It's the last Harmontown of 2013, get ready for some Christmas magic. Anatoly gets on stage nearly nude, Duncan Trussell talks Christmas as a mushroom cult, Adam Goldberg nearly murders everyone, Jeff Davis hates Paul McCartney and Rob Schrab jumps in on D&D. Happy Holidays and we'll see you next year!

episodes.title: 82- Jim Belushi's Basement (with Mitch Hurwitz)
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon brings Arrested Development's creator Mitch Hurwitz on stage to talk shop about TV. Later Kumail returns and the whole thing ends with an epic D&D session. Quit reading already and press play!

episodes.title: 81 - Hot Dog With Lettuce (Laraine Newman, Dr. Chris Ryan)
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon jumps right into a drop in from original Saturday Night Live cast member Laraine Newman which merges into a visit from controversial author Dr. Chris Ryan to delves into polygamy and the very nature of our sexuality. In D&D, Spencer gives up.

episodes.title: 80 - Harmontown At Largo (Justin Roiland, John Oliver, Sarah Chalke)
episodes.summary:
In conjunction with Adult Swim and Starburns Industries, HARMONTOWN Live at Largo Coronet Theatre!
Featuring Justin Roiland, John Oliver and Sarah Chalke!
(Presented in 128kbps Stereo)

episodes.title: 79 - Dangle, Dipping and Heel Popping
episodes.summary: After some women demonstrate foot fetish techniques that audibly won't make any sense to you, dear listener, the enigmatic Brody Stevens joins Harmontown for the first time. Later, Mayor Harmon is inducted into a prestigious alliance and Kumail returns to D&D after a month long hiatus. It's a beautiful sprawling Harmontown, come on down.

episodes.title: 78 - Earthshine
episodes.summary: For the second time in Harmontown history a bottle of moonshine appears. It's Integrity vs. dishonesty, Baby Boomers vs. Gen X'ers vs. Millennials, it's Mayor Harmon vs. the bathroom at Meltdown Comics, it's Adam  vs. Levi, it's Harmontown vs. the world!

episodes.title: 77 - Carpool Diem
episodes.summary: In the wake of Lou Reed's passing, in which this episode is dedicated to; a sad, stripped down, sleepy and introspective Velvet Harmontown. Plus, the introduction of Harmontown's new character "Johnny Jackhammer." In DnD, the gang is helpless to watch Yearch "less than zero."

episodes.title: 76 - Hug Me, Hug Me, Hug Me
episodes.summary: The room is packed with Communicon fans and two of them are asked by Mayor Harmon to come on stage and discuss a recent internet exchange about why they feel Dan should "stop talking." A lengthy game of D&D then ensues.

episodes.title: 75 - Selling Like Hot Snakes
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon is joined once again by guest Rob Schrab and Erin McGathy plays the role of Comptroller. Spontaneous combustion, peeing your pants and letters from reddit await you in this weeks Harmontown!

episodes.title: 74 - Morality
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon tries to examine our ethical boundaries, but when that sounds too much like going to bat for pedophiles, everyone starts high fiving themselves for not wanting to do it with babies

episodes.title: 73 - From Kennedy's Assassination, To The Beatles
episodes.summary: Don Cheatle's speech at the Emmys leaves Mayor Harmon pondering. Also, spider monsters, the Beef Fungus Bill game and co-creator of Channel 101 Rob Schrab sits in on D&D!

episodes.title: 72 - Jib Jab Squeeb Squab
episodes.summary: Rejoice! Kumail is back and joins Dan and Jeff on stage along with comedians John Roy, James Adomian and the entire front row.

episodes.title: 71 - Push The Button, Pull The Chain
episodes.summary: The Mayor uses his iHarmon to knock down an entire show agenda that includes topics like Premium Gas and what Harmontown should do this year for Halloween when Comptroller Jeff Davis says no to his idea for 15 minutes straight. Later, Erin doesn't understand Grand Theft Auto V and an attractive man in a wheel chair joins the stage for a game of Pathfinder!

episodes.title: 70 - Gone Fishin'
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon, now equipped with his trusty new invention, is joined by Johnny Pemberton to break down prank phone calls. Afterwards a visit from "The Tumor Lady" and then later on, the topic of fishing for compliments becomes a major issue for everyone on stage. Mostly Erin, who challenges Spencer in this nearly lost episode.

episodes.title: 69 - Cobra Customer Service
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon issues an edict to wait staff, proclaims his eternal love for Erin and signs off on gay weddings.

episodes.title: 68 - Jolly Rodger
episodes.summary: In the middle of working on Community 501, a very tired Mayor Harmon takes to a crowd of Harmenians and revels in their eccentricities. In D&D, an Ogre cums.

episodes.title: 67 - Click Here For Bacardi
episodes.summary: Mayor Pet psychology is discussed. Then the usual topics of race and terrorism. Then crap gets real about anarchy on the moon.

episodes.title: 66 - Frequently I Am A Woman In My Dreams
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon has got nothing. This prompts Kumail and Erin to join the stage for some dream interpretation and penis trauma. In D&D, Sharpie dies.

episodes.title: 65 - Tim Tums Are Where Cake and Vodka Go
episodes.summary: Harmon talks to Matt Dwyer about being a better interviewer than Mayor Harmon, who no longer needs to be good at anything because he survived an endoscopy.  In D&D: Frost Giant politics.

episodes.title: 64 - I Would Be Mega Black (James Urbaniak)
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon strives to understand whether or not he's a 9/11 conspiracy theorist with special guest James Urbaniak.  Also: race and stuff.

episodes.title: 63 - Everyone in the World is Stupid
episodes.summary: New editions of Things Dan Can't Complain About and Connor's Conundrums, a chat with aneurysm survivor Siike and a violent fight with Spencer about "meta gaming."

episodes.title: 62 - Blinking 12:00
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon has nothing to discuss so he opens it to the floor.  Super powers are debated.  Gifts are given.  A special guest returns to D&D.

episodes.title: 61 - USS Hubris
episodes.summary: Titanic Sinclair and Mars Argo help examine the internet's war on the self.   Comptroller McGathy refs a game of "Spencer or Goldberg" between  Mayor Harmon and Kumail.

episodes.title: 60 - Us Of The Dangling Wee-Wee
episodes.summary: In which it asserted by Harmontown, that Fathers are important. Guest starring Spencer's Dad.

episodes.title: 59 - Writing Tips From A Jerk
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon tells us how to not write. Also discussed: Wikileaks, Disabilities, Ben Affleck and puppies.

episodes.title: 58 - I'm Like Very Science
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon explains why an episode was lost; soon to be uncontextually quoted frivolity ensues. Jeff reveals he's psychic;  Kumail's resultant bewilderment preempts D&D.

episodes.title: 57 - Blood on the Corn
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon and Guest Comptroller Goldthwait examine their own bodies, Dan's drinking, Jeremy Piven, Bigfoot and their likely deaths by significant other. In D&D, the heroes continue to fight their shadow selves.

episodes.title: 56 - Language is Thought and Spiders are Black People
episodes.summary: An all around provocapalooza surrounding language, race, religion, science, bugs, moms and fake dinosaurs. In D&D, the characters awake in Ye Olde Arena Milieu.

episodes.title: 55 - Shahruz the Web Guru
episodes.summary: After a well meaning stranger poisons the audience with beef fungus, Chinese Ironman, Eddie Murphy, John Landis and Yakov Smirnoff are discussed. In D&D, everyone dies.

episodes.title: 54 - Go, Marbles, Go! (Duncan Trussell, Greg Proops)
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon, sore from softball practice, enlists the aid of Duncan Trussell and Greg Proops to keep the meeting moving.  Topics include virtual reality, dead mothers and Jaws 4.  In Dungeons and Dragons, Erin summons her first monkey.

episodes.title: 53 - National Tragedy Special (Kumail Nanjiani)
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon finds out about terrorism after everyone else. Plus: cake making, tentanus, Kumail, and making love to spiders!

episodes.title: 52 - By the Power of Bored Audience Skull! (Kumail Nanjiani)
episodes.summary: In which Mayor Harmon explores everything that's already been explored about the topics of Road House, Roger Ebert and Skeletor. Plus: Kumail Nanjiani, Drunk Spencer and the final word on nipple size.

episodes.title: 51 - Bikers Without Bikes (Robin Williams, Bobcat Goldthwait)
episodes.summary: Bobcat Goldthwait returns with his friend Robin Williams and an amazingly sad story from a very dark carnival. Then, Robin and Bobcat leave, and it's kind of hard to follow them, so Mayor Harmon plays D&D and talks to a girl about sexism or something.

episodes.title: 50 - Joe Jackson: Steppin' Out
episodes.summary: In honor of the 50th episode, Harmon drinks too much five hour energy, Genevieve Pearson teaches us to fabricate reality and Kumail proposes to three-time-wife Emily. D&D is bunch of garbage, but then, and, admittedly, this is Harmon saying this, but: BEST RAP EVER. Enjoy.

episodes.title: 49 - Jock Jams and Pearl Jams
episodes.summary: Man versus lion, Space Jam versus Goonies, Leprechaun versus his own sexuality.  Brian W. Collins retires his horror movie blog.  Kumail Nanjiani and the rest of the D&D party finish their battle with specific parts of a dragon.

episodes.title: 48 - Felicity Wackamole (Doug Benson, Kumail Nanjiani)
episodes.summary: Featuring Doug Benson and Kumail Nanjiani.  Topics include Gene Hackman, emphysema, sharks, cereal, Thalidomide, Wreck it Ralph, burn victims, Dracula, Special Olympics, regular Olympics, Bruce Villanch, missing electronics and law enforcement.  The D&D party flirts with sleep studies, then fights a dragon.

episodes.title: 47 - Procrasturbation
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon suggests a new, fecal approach to morality. Other topics include Halle Berry, Superman and accents. In D&D, the gang runs afoul of snake men and each other.

episodes.title: 46 - Neigh Means Yay
episodes.summary: 'Rick and Morty' writer Ryan Ridley drops by, 'Real Abed' Gheith pitches his insane restuarant and Kumail Nanjiani reveals secrets to brown acting. In D&D: the party climbs into a hole.

episodes.title: 45 - Dan Took a Shower (Kumail Nanjiani, Bobcat Goldthwait)
episodes.summary: A discussion of hygiene heats up with Kumail Nanjiani, then boils over when Bobcat Goldthwait drops by.  In D&D, zombies attack while Quark engages in advanced animal husbandry.  This fabulous episode is unedited so we will just warn you of a small glitch with the mayor's mic a few minutes in that lasts but a moment.

episodes.title: 44 - Dudes and Goo (DC Pierson, Kumail Nanjiani)
episodes.summary: After a few false starts, it turns out Mayor Harmon may be suffering from a show-threatening case of  homecoming confidence, but when special guests D.C Pierson and Kumail Nanjiani join, the meeting erupts into an awesome discussion of drugs, religion, Spencer, Hannibal Lechter and octopus sex.  In D&D: Sharpie and Mulraine seal the deal.

episodes.title: 43 - Harmoncountry: Los Angeles (Bobcat Goldthwait, Marc Maron, Duncan Trussell)
episodes.summary: Looking back on his tour, non-heroic Mayjor Harmon asks what have I learned (spoiler: he doesn't know) with friends Bobcat Goldthwait, Marc Maron and Duncan Trussell in an epic show at L.A's Egyptian Theater.

episodes.title: 42 - Harmoncountry: San Francisco, CA
episodes.summary: The tour ends at the golden gate, where freedom to live is achieved by getting drunk, talking nonsense, meeting strangers and, well, you know the forumla.

episodes.title: 41 - Harmoncountry: Portland, OR
episodes.summary: Mayoral Master Harmon strides boldly across the return threshold and declares Spencer God. Then he raps and dicks around with people in the audience. It doesn't sound like much on paper but it's a pretty great episode.

episodes.title: 40 - Harmoncountry: Salt Lake City, UT
episodes.summary: Harmontown is reborn in a strange land of complex liquor laws, polarized religion and Kevin Nealon photos. Plus: Sports Corner, Fart Corner, odor dating and weird rants!

episodes.title: 39 - Harmoncountry: Denver, CO
episodes.summary: High atop the nation, in Omlette Country, Comptroller Davis returns. Topics include cheese sticks, sports, beat boxing, dungeons, dragons and crazy people.

episodes.title: 38 - Harmoncountry: Kansas City, KS
episodes.summary: Kansas finds itself at the center of the biggest disaster since Dorothy's twister when Mayor Harmon and Erin McGathy conduct the worst town meeting of the tour. This episode is unedited because I have no idea what I'd cut without cutting the entire thing.

episodes.title: 37 - Harmoncountry: Minneapolis, MN
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon and Guest Comptroller McGathy interface with Twin Town from injured tendon to badly placed sound effect. Former Dead Alewives member Sean McKenna raps. Joyfully unedited episode.

episodes.title: 36 - Harmoncountry: Madison, WI
episodes.summary: Atonement turns to struggle within a dark cavern. Dan's friend loses an appendage. His Improv mentor is there, but Jeff is leaving?! The audience shouts weird things! Latinos are everywhere!

episodes.title: 35 - Harmoncountry: Chicago, IL
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon starts Atoning With The Father when he presents a day in his fantasy TV writer life, confronts a drunk Darth Vader, then adopts a 15 year old version of himself. The night ends with an impromptu rap battle before new Harmenian Kahleel takes the throne.

episodes.title: 34 - Harmoncountry: Bloomington, IN
episodes.summary: In honor of his Midwestern heritage, The Mayor puts a town meeting straight up the middle and over the plate, with sports talk, a cosmic meditation and an in depth discussion of science and religion with some of Indiana's greatest, drunkest minds!

episodes.title: 33 - Harmoncountry: Pittsburgh, PA
episodes.summary: The Harmontown tour "meets its goddess" in a featureless black box theatre, where Dan cries, arouses himself, tells a joke and gets in a fight with Erin.  Unedited episode.

episodes.title: 32 - Harmoncountry: Arlington, VA
episodes.summary: The mayor and comptroller spend their night in the X Files capitol investigating ghosts, aliens, incest and 9-11 before playing D&D with all black people.

episodes.title: 31 - Harmoncountry: Providence, RI
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon used the country's smallest state to tackle the country's biggest issues - suicide and race - before remembering someone double booked the room so he has to leave.

episodes.title: 30 - Harmoncountry: Sommerville, MA
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon and Comptroller Davis begin the show like any other - discussing the city's auto theft statistics.  What comes next is 80+ minutes of insanity, featuring Adam Goldberg's brothers, Erin and Dan's sex life and much, much, sooooo much more.

episodes.title: 29 - Harmoncountry: Brooklyn, NY
episodes.summary: New York's biggest borrough rolls out the longest red carpet in Harmoncountry yet.  Jeff and Dan improvise a Black Mexican guest's screenplay.  Jason Sudeikis drops by and jumps into D&D with astonishing vigor.  Dan does a bad job of supporting Erin's PMS, then stage dives.

episodes.title: 28 - Harmoncountry: Charlotte, NC
episodes.summary: A quiet military bunker in Charlotte known as The Comedy Zone is the site of a kinder, gentler town meeting than Nashville's booze-drenched hootenanny.  Mayor Harmon attempts to write a constitution and learns about the deep seated, low-stakes conflict between the Carolinas.  In D&D, the band reunites aboard a spaceship and Erin shames a loud lady.

episodes.title: 27 - Harmoncountry: Nashville, TN
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon chooses Music City, USA as the place to enter the "drunk Brian Wilson" phase of his podcasting career.  Is his mistake the pre-show Jaggerbombs or the mid-show moonshine?  In any case, let this episode stand as a cautionary tale.

episodes.title: 26 - Harmoncountry: Atlanta, GA
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon regales the "Paris of Georgia" with historic knowledge, general trivia and mad rapping science.  Topics include his armpits and race.

episodes.title: 25 - Harmoncountry: Austin, TX
episodes.summary: What else would Mayor Harmon discuss in Austin other than Politics, Mexican food, Hey Yah by Outkast and pooping?  In D&D: a friend's dark secret is revealed.

episodes.title: 24 - Harmoncountry: Phoenix, Arizona
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon begins his tour feeling way more insecure than the kind-hearted heroes of a new city.  A Harmontown theme with an awesome hook starts getting workshopped.  In D&D, the heroes fight cylinders.

episodes.title: 23 - Turtle Panties
episodes.summary: Harmontown's last show before the tour becomes a star studded bon voyage.  Eric Idle teaches Dan to write songs, Patton Oswalt teaches him the meaning of fear and Ryan Stiles teaches him that fighting displacer beasts takes 45 minutes.

episodes.title: 22 - Nanu Nanu, I'm Racist
episodes.summary: An impromptu Fellowship of the Nerds is assembled to explain how to break The Hobbit into three movies.  Jury duty stories!  Adam Goldberg's roommate!

episodes.title: 21 - Adventurtunity Mobisode!
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon does his Bane impression and practices getting booed in various cities for the upcoming tour.  In D&D: the heroes finally encounter Sharpie's dad.

episodes.title: 20 - Flesh Knife
episodes.summary: Note: the audience was not mic'd this episode.  More horrible rapping, a new character named Big Red, a phone call to Chevy Chase and a conversation with Adam Goldberg.  In D&D: our heroes fall into a pit!

episodes.title: 19 - Everyone's a Rapper!
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon comes up spittin' decidedly unmad fire.  We meet a mysterious lady in the audience that can only say "no."  No D&D this week but Spencer rules the day just the same.  Adam Goldberg takes a swipe at having a segment.  Dan raps EVEN MORE.  New Harmenian "Misha" takes the stage and does some standup.  Dan and Jeff rap battle!

episodes.title: 18 - Sand Pollution: The Journals of Young Morrisey
episodes.summary: Dan reads from his magical adolescent journals, casting a magical spell of adolescent depression over the entire audience and the dungeons and dragons session.  So he brings up a depressed Harmenian and attempts to cure him.  But by then he's pretty drunk.

episodes.title: 17 - Grumblesnakes!
episodes.summary: It's election night fever when Dan and Jeff realize that the episode will air long after the election.  Clearly a devout Democrat, Dan complains about his hired help before bringing up a real live woman to referee history's least informed Harry Potter trivia competition.  Plus: transitional D&D!  Freestyle rapping!  Not knowing how to end the show!

episodes.title: 16 - A Four Day March to the Butt's Expanse
episodes.summary: It's a Jareth-palooza as Harmenians descend on Hollywood dressed as David Bowie in Labyrinth for Halloween.  Other topics include almost nothing!

episodes.title: 15 - Don't Ask Black People Time Travel Questions
episodes.summary: Dan has nothing, so he answers twitter questions.  Adam Goldberg takes over the show, then, Dan interviews ethnic people.  Plus: in D&D world:  the party levels up!

episodes.title: 14 - Tyler Perry's Antisemitic Pickle Ziggurat (10.15.12)
episodes.summary: An unflinching examination of Dan's mustache absorption becomes a flinching examination of Harmontown regular Adam Goldberg.  Plus: special guest Steve Agee drops by for a discussion of airline food and the ridiculous infiltration of Admiral Darkstar's stronghold.

episodes.title: 13 - Back To The Future Part Kush (10.01.12)
episodes.summary: Dan complains about things he's not allowed to complain about, then outs himself as the world's laziest gay rights and medical marijuana advocate.  Plus, in D&D world: nothing happens!

episodes.title: 12 - Death, Fascism and the Pursuit of Not Remaking Robocop
episodes.summary: Special guest Greg Proops returns!  The question of what happens after you die remains unanswered, but tangents include mental illness, poverty and misunderstood Van Halen lyrics.  Meanwhile, in D&D world, Sharpie and Quark claim their Embermauler bounty, buy horses and do improv in a forest with an old unicorn friend.

episodes.title: 11 - Tylenol With Codeine (9.17.12)
episodes.summary: The first appearance of Greg Proops provokes a fit of Mayor Harmon's pointless political rants and a D&D adventure that shall forever be remembered as involving unicorn pee.

episodes.title: 10 - A Tuppence or a Shilling for Your Wainscotting (9.10.12)
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon and Guest Comptroller Erin McGathy discuss Knight Rider, Alf and anxiety, then play a quick round of Dungeons and Dragons before getting into a huge fight about movies and breaking up.

episodes.title: 9 - Examine Before You Fight (9.4.12)
episodes.summary: A discussion of the clarinet and nine eleven is briefly interrupted by an amazing D&D adventure before proceeding into an indictment of the Hugo Awards and concluding with a demonstration of how hard it is to conclude.

episodes.title: 8 - Cleft In Twain! (8.27.12)
episodes.summary: Mayor Harmon grapples with fame and exposes The Family Feud; Comptroller Davis grapples with and exposes Harmon's shocking inability to tell jokes and the roleplaying Adventures of Sharpie and Quark begin.

episodes.title: 7 - Cranky Mayors, Pink Hairs and Shoelace Cares (8.20.12)
episodes.summary: An especially antsy crowd turns Harmontown's meeting into a flippin' town meeting, pushing our fearless leader from musings on infidelity to contemplations of suicide.  Plus: Dungeonmaster Spencer unveils the boys' characters!

episodes.title: 6 - Atonement with the Mannequins and Butts (8.16.12)
episodes.summary: Sometimes it happens. Sometimes an innocent story about junior high proceeds down a road of perversion straight to where the sun doesn't shine.  Also: Spencer collects info for Harmon and Davis' D&D characters, and special guest Rob Schrab tells a story...about his butt.

episodes.title: 5 - Confessions Of An Alcoholic Mars Rover (8.7.12)
episodes.summary: Jeff blows the whistle on NASA's secret agenda and Dan blows surprise guest Chris Hardwick!

episodes.title: 4 - The Technology Of N-Words (7.31.12)
episodes.summary: A discussion of something the Scottish call a "Wizard Sleeve" is ever-so-briefly interrupted by racism, robots, and a visit from something Erin McGathy calls a "game corner."

episodes.title: 3 - If They Have Cubs, We're Already Dead (7.23.12)
episodes.summary: An unusually quiet night in Harmontown gives way to eruptions of arm wrestling, wolf hunting, dungeon mastering and child abuse.

episodes.title: 2 - The Inception Of Girlfriends (7.16.12)
episodes.summary: While Jeff Davis works abroad, Guest Comptroller Erin McGathy ("This Feels Terrible") joins Mayor Harmon for an in depth look at overrated masterpieces, passive aggressive text messages and how to destroy someone else's relationship on stage.

episodes.title: 1 - Achieve Weightlessness (6.16.12)
episodes.summary: It's a special night at Harmontown when Mayor Harmon decides the goal is to "achieve weightlessness" and establish Harmontown's real purpose.  One hour, thirty tangents, two emails from Harmon's big brother and that goal remains unachieved, but a legendary theme park death does finally get its own theme song.
